FEMALE
. As male except for the following character states. Eye, facets of equal size (
Fig. 28
); dichoptic. Frons black ground colour; with greyish brown pollinosity, except in dorsal third where dark brown; covered with short intermixed pale and dark pile, in dorsal part more dark pile; rugose area shining brown to yellow-brown, occupying less than one-third width and equal in height to at most twice the ocellar triangle. Face with orange-brown patches. Wing (
Fig. 60
), fumose area sometimes more extensive. Extension and coloration of orange-brown markings variable, sometimes terga 2 and 3 completely black-brown.
